Chapter Six:<br>
<br>
Saffryn's Journal - Monday, Feb. 23, 3178<br>
<br>
Upon climbing up the Orc Hill, I saw it aflame in blue fire. Quickly my sword joined in with the fray, not a single wood-elf but myself, but we fought well together none-the-less. I half-elven bard, Ramiie was near my same season in his training, a high-elf finger-wagger named Tellurian, and an incredible high-level, high-elf named Hypnosis. I am in awe of her. <br>
My first vision of her was wearing an enchantment to look as though she were a werewolf, her howls bringing chills to my arms. In dropping her illusion she appeared the palest high-elf I have ever seen, snow-white hair and the most beautiful eyes. Though her face wore the same hautery as most high-elves, as Tellurian did too, I found that in fighting a common foe, they were both concentrated and strong, dropping all ideals of being better than my kind. <br>
<br>
Never once did they short me on any protection spells as I fought with my sword and feeble magic, and Ramiie fought with his scimitar. Nay, in fact, it was hard pressed to convince them to loot the corpses so that whatever gods the orcs believe in could take their bodies away. I found it quite difficult to target my flames at the live ones for all the bodies on the ground.<br>
<br>
The experience I gathered tonight was unmeasurable, and I will be proud to present Master Canlor in Kaladim with my prize of three full bags of belts.<br>
<br>
<br>
