Saffryn's Journal - Reflections<br>
<br>
I have had a particulary hard week. Death has come my way many times and I would have met death many more had it not been for my uncle, Gareth Pineshade. Of course, he is Guard Pineshade when he is on duty, but he doesn't hesitate to grace me with a wink from under his helm when he's saving my sorry butt from one too many orcs pounding my backside.<br>
<br>
I had dinner with him and my aunt this week and he had a rather frightening tale to tell. He says that there are many other planets in the universe inhabited by many diverse creatures, many of which die only once and it is forever. While Tunare graces us with returning us to where our soul is bound with a healthy body and discards our old one once we gather our things, there are other gods not as forgiving of our, well, over-stretching of our abilities, shall we say.<br>
<br>
On some worlds, says Uncle Pineshade, the soul is separated forever upon that single death and returns to the place of their god. Still, on other worlds, the soul, he says, rests for a time and then enters a new baby's body to start all over. <br>
<br>
I cannot imagine having to start all over again as a babe. How on Norrath could anyone learn from their lessons like that? I'd forever be making the same mistakes if I could not remember making the one that brought me death. <br>
<br>
On a better note, I have not seen Bramblepants for sometime. There is rumor that he had to suddenly return home, wherever that is. I wonder how he weaseled the deed from the old Prince that once owned that garish lodge. <br>
<br>
I, no doubt, will have nightmares again tonight, on dying once and forever and waking as a helpless infant screaming up into the face of Sir Bramblepants with those ever present twigs in his hair.<br>
