Prince Wardrym stands deep in thought, staring at the last of the glowing ashes that had been his mother's funeral pyre. His father has long left to attend an irreverant celebration with the other Princes. Turning slowly, his thoughts turn to plans, and he eventually ascends the steps to his father's home. He doesn't have to go near his father's reception room to hear the loud boasting and bravado. <br>
