Glasses are clinked loudly at the salute to successfully convincing the King to raise the taxes upon the wood-elf Barons. Cheers have been celebrated everyday as the Princes raise their ideals of &quot;custom of living&quot; and increase their heaps of profits. &quot;Will the celebrations ever end? Will the burden upon the Barons ever break their backs,&quot; Wardrym mumbles to himself.<br>
