He reflects on what he has just read before going on to read what Tunare has set forth in the text lying before him wrapped in the ancient leather of elk. <p><center> <img src="http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/theorderofthewhitehand/images/oldsig.jpg"><br><b>Saffryn, Ranger of Norrath<b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaffryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saffryn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f95.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/02 11:24:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f75.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Exodus</span><hr size=1> &quot;Daina,&quot; Ward stops his housekeeper as she drops off his lunch in his study, &quot;What do you know of the Exodus from Tunaria to Fadwer?&quot;<br>
<br>
Daina pauses thoughtfully, &quot;Well now, the whole lot of Eldritch were run out of Tunaria with a drought brought on my Solusek Ro, I believe, yes?  First the woodies had to leave their tree homes and they crowded into the cities, then we all came here as Tunaria turned quickly into what we now call the Desert of Ro.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes,&quot; replies Ward, &quot;but what happened when we got to Faydwer?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well you had more education than I did, you being a prince and all,&quot; she states at which Ward frowns.  &quot;But if you want the tale of the commen folk, I'll give it to ya straight enough.&quot;<br>
