&quot;Though I believe you trust in an untrue god, I am not here to judge that. You have a man who is cursed and you wish him cured. Whether you call it &quot;love&quot; or &quot;chosen&quot;, you stand by him, and I can respect that. I have a task to secure a necklace, and you offer to return that necklace if I find the pages. Do not believe me foolish in trusting you....I do not trust that easily, however, I shall give you a certain...space...in which we may temporarily be a peace until our mutual task is completed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You and I, Shaede, will find those pages, heal your man, and return a family heirloom....after that....we shall dissolve our peace and return to our battles....Deal?&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
