<br>
It had been a very eventful couple of weeks months for Saffryn, between reaching her 9th Season with her excursion to Freeport for the firebeetle eyes to the recent encounters at the guildhall and accepting the quest for Windam's necklace.  <br>
<br>
Saffryn decides it's time to get beyond her 11th Season and earn the right to learn Meditation and decides to set forth inth Crushbone.  Having acquired a shackle key, she starts sneaking towards the back of the Orc Hold to where the slaves are being kept when she is suddenly struck down by two slavers.  Realizing her stupidity at letting her guard down, she must further chastize herself when she realizes she still had her soul bound in Freeport.<br>
<br>
&quot;Stupid, stupid, stupid !&quot; she exclaims within the guild hive-thought.  Aegeras answers her with a worried, &quot;You okay, Saffryn?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, yes, just bearing the consequences of my own stupidity.  I just let myself get cornered by two Orc Slavers in Crushbone and I left myself soul-bound in Freeport.  Just heading for the boat back.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't.  Don't get on the boat, I'll port you back.&quot;<br>
<br>
Not wanting to put the kind man out and take him away from his own training, &quot;No, No, Aegplant, er, Aegeras, m'lord.  This is my fault..I was stupid.  I can take the boat, it'll teach me a lesson.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I insist, and I am no lord.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I'm sorry, you've told me that before.  It's a habit you know, Sir Aeggo, er, Aegcentric, um, Aegeras.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not a sir either.  Meet me in East Freeport.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well if you insist, on my way.&quot;<br>
<br>
Running to not keep the man waiting, she runs right past him and he spins her around.  &quot;Now join me, Saff,&quot; he says, and with that he opens a portal and takes her hand and together they step in and are whisked away to the rings of Steamfront.<br>
<br>
From there they run together through Lesser Faydark when she is spoken to in the elven mind by a young one who has just obtained his Ressurection spell.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take the Res, Saff, I'll meet you at Crushbone.&quot;<br>
<br>
Not knowing why Aegaras has not returned to his own training, she welcomes his aid as he watchers her back while she re-memorizes her spells, dons her gear from her corpse* (how this is explained is in Willowswood Part One) and smiles from ear to ear at Aegaras.  &quot;I can't thank you enough, Aegnoodle.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's nothing, lets see what's going on at the Trainer&quot; he says.  Quickly he protects her with an onslaught of spells as she takes the trainer down, an Orc that would normally be much too difficult for her.  On her first assault on the Trainer, she is rewarded with the Shiny Brass Shield. She squeels in delight and hugs Aeg tightly about the neck.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're family now, Saff, it's nothing.&quot; grins Aegaras.  &quot;Lets get you the Emporer&quot; he adds, you could use some chainmail.&quot;<br>
<br>
Before Saffryn can move, open mouthed and hiding her quaking knees, Aegaras is back with the Emporer at the mouth of the Crushbone cave.  &quot;Take him Saffryn,&quot; Aegaras cheers, keeping her protected and asking others to back away and let Saffryn have the fight alone.  Weak from just taking the Trainer, Aegaras has to help Saffryn finish him off and the Emperor has empty pockets.  They both rest and rebuild their strength and mana before running to the wall just outside the bridge to the castle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wait here, Saffryn,&quot; says Aeg, and she obeys, goosebumps tingling up her spine and hardening her nipples thinking of the swordplay she is about to engage in. Straight away Aegeras is back, Saffryn is fully loaded with protection buffs from Aegaras.  The sword play begins.  She dodges many blows, wears the Emperor down with the Thistle coat cast upon her by Aeg, and slashes and kicks her way with the Strength of Earth and Skin of Steel until the Emporor turns his back to run.  Firmly planted into the ground with a casting of snare, the Emperor is trapped, and with the final blow, Saffryn peels away the magical dwarven ringmail tunic.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Aegquiche, I have earned my twelfth season this day, a much sought after shield, and a beautiful coat of ringmail, all because of you,&quot; she tries not to gush.  &quot;How can I ever repay you kindness?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, remember, Saff, it's nothing.  We're Dragons.  We're family.&quot;<br>
<br>
Saffryin sighs, &quot;Well, then I guess at the very least I should stop flubbing up your name...Aegaras.&quot;<br>
<br>
The day at an end, she hugs Aegaras and pounds his back soundly the way she hugs one of her many cousins.  Both grinning at each other, Saffryn flips her sword deftly over her wrist, sweeps the sword with a bow, and then blows a bubble and snaps the tree-tar gum she's chewing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Until next- time, my new cousin.  May Tunare always watch your back, and if not, call me and I shall be there.&quot; <p><center> <img src="http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/theorderofthewhitehand/images/oldsig.jpg"><br><b>Saffryn, Ranger of Norrath<b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaffryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saffryn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f95.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/28/02 9:34:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaffryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saffryn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f95.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 12:24:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=531.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f75.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Politics of Elves</span><hr size=1> The Meeting:<br>
<br>
Saffryn is sharing cornered with her aunt and uncle Hearthwood at their tavern recounting the exciting day she had hunting with Aegeras when in walks &quot;Mr. Bramblepants&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah Gah, there he is again, everywhere I go,&quot; Saffy says to her aunt and uncle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who, Wardrym? He's a nice fellow, let me introduce you,&quot; says her uncle, Manlawen, as he motions for Wardrym to come over as Saffryn cringes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hail Wardrym Nobleheart, I'd like you to meet my niece, Saffryn Trueshot.  Saffy, this is Ward,&quot; says Manlawen.<br>
<br>
As Ward bows to Saffy she quips &quot;Nobleheart, not Nobleheart of the Felwithe Paladin's guild?  You dunna look like any hauty, er high-elf to me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Saffy!  Ya need nah be rude!&quot; says her aunt, Uuilanu.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry, yur lordship, but the Koada'Dal have nah been very well thought of as late with the rise in taxes and all,&quot; exclaims Saffy with a raised brow.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's alright m'lady, I completely understand.  I am in disagreement with workings of Felwithe, myself.  As for my looks, well, I find the clothing and the lifestyle of the Feir'Dal to be much more comfortable and practical...and I do not cling to any titles so please, no &quot;lordship&quot; here.<br>
<br>
With a look and a grin to each other, Saffryn's aunt and uncle move back to take care of other customers coming into the tavern and leave the two to get to know each other.  Watching them go, Ward purses his lips together and decides to plunge in.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, now that we've met, m'lady&quot; begins Ward and is interrupted by Saffryn, &quot;No m'lady's here either.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;All right then,&quot; Ward continues, &quot;Saffryn.  I've been looking for you.<br>
<br>
&quot;Following me, ya mean,&quot; as she takes a drag from her ale.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well yes, I had to see if you had the qualities I'm looking for.  I need your help.&quot; says Ward.<br>
<br>
&quot;My help?  What would a Lord of Nobleheart need with a lowly woodie like me?&quot; smarts off Saffy.  Then remembering her manners, &quot;Sorry.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;This must be strictly confidential, on your word as a Feir'Dal,&quot; says Ward.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well if you hold the word of a Feir'Dal to any value, yes, I give you my word.  What is this help you need.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a deep breath, he looks Saffy in the eye and says, &quot;I think the Book of Law has been corrupted.  It's quite obvious that the Koada'Dal use it to their full advantage over the Baronrys, but I think that they have an extra advantage.  I think they have altered the words that were set forth by our Goddess, Tunare.  I mean to find out the truth of this and set things right.&quot;<br>
<br>
Looking astonished, &quot;Now why on Norrath would you want to do that?  You're own father would have you gutted from jaw to groin, I'd wager.  What reason would you have to go against your own people for the sake of mine?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Because I have a secret of my own that I'm not ready to reveal at this time,&quot; answers Ward.  &quot;I've taken Willowswood as my own and I have no intention of following in my father's footsteps, save that of my paladin training.  He was very cruel to my mother and sent her to an early grave.  The Princes live in an endless cycle of debauchery and celebration in their luck at being born in the lap of Felwithe.   It sickens me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Really hate Prince Joren, eh?&quot; says Saff.  &quot;You are in good company.  He lauds his heavy hand over the Emerald Warriors and leaves them to do the dirty work while the Felwithe warriors get the better duties and the Paladins act the officers and rule them all.  So...why do you need me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The original Book of Law was magically written by Tunare, herself and cannot be added to or anything taken away.  It's been hundreds of years since the public has seen the Book.  We all see copies, but only a select few have access to the original.  I mean to have a look at that tome, see what it REALLY says so I can decide from there what to do.&quot; says Wardrym.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who are the select few who can see the book,&quot; Saff asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Only the guild-leaders and their heirs, five leaders and their heirs.&quot; replies Wardrym<br>
<br>
&quot;Well you're the heir, are you not, Prince Joren is the guild-leader of Pally's.&quot; says Saffryn.<br>
<br>
&quot;My father does not quite trust me.  We haven't been close, ever.  He has showed no intention of training me to follow him as his heir even though I have been publicly and lawfully named as such.  He does not bring me to any of their political functions, and has not given me access to any 'sensitive' matters. &quot; says Wardrym.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, you are going to sneak your way in?&quot; says Saffryn.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes&quot; replies Wardrym.<br>
<br>
&quot;Any traps?  Secret Passages?  Magic locks?&quot; asks Saffryn.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes&quot; replies Wardrym.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then what you need is a rogue from the Scout's guild, not me,&quot; she says as she begins to stand.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wait!, there's more,&quot; Ward says quickly.<br>
<br>
Sitting she says, &quot;I'm listening.&quot;<br>
<br>
Nervously he continues, &quot;If I'm right about what I've discovered so far, your family is involved.  I need you, a Trueshot to get to the Book,&quot; he lies as Saffryn looks at him unconvinced.<br>
<br>
With a heavy sigh and crossed fingers that she'll accept the false tale he's about to weave, he continues, &quot;The Trueshots weren't always rangers, Saffryn.  There is a book of lineage that came with us from Tunaria.  In it, it shows that before the Houses were divided into Koada'Dal and Feir'dal and specialized, there were Trueshot wizards.  Some of the Trueshots lived in Takish-Hur.  The majority lived in the forest and that's why your family house went with the Fier'dal, but there was one very important Trueshot wizard, the wizard that set the final lock that seals the sacred tome, our Book of Law.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There is a secret trick to the lock,&quot; Wardrym contines, &quot;that all the of the Koada'Dal heirs learn upon their father or mother's death. I don't know what the secret is that trips the lock without setting off the traps, however, the lock is said to answer to an Heir of the Trueshot wizard without question. I need YOU.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Okay,&quot; says Saffryn, &quot;let's say I believe this, hypothetically, why me - why not one of my brothers.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Because your brothers are older and busy with more important conflicts in Norrath than just the Crushbone Orcs,&quot; Ward answers.  &quot;I doubt they'd give me the time of day.  On top of that, with age, everyone in the Baronry's have a love of taking everything to committee and having meetings before deciding on anything.  If I approached one of your brothers, next thing I'd know there would be a meeting of the Baronry's about it and nothing would get done.  You know that. On top of that, it would leak out from there to the Koada'Dal and my plans would be blown.  I'd never get to the truth.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And you don't think I'LL take it to commitee?&quot; Saffryn asks wryly.<br>
<br>
&quot;No&quot; answers Wardrym.<br>
<br>
